4. Phase 3: Continental Integration (2030-2032)

4.1 2030: Global Network Integration

4.1.1 Global Network Operations Center (GNOC)

```
Location: Geographically distributed (3 primary, 3 backup)
Primary Centers:
  - Center 1: North America (Colorado, USA)
  - Center 2: Europe (Switzerland)
  - Center 3: Asia (Singapore)

Each Center Specifications:
  - Size: 50,000 sq ft operations floor
  - Staff: 200 operations personnel per shift
  - Displays: 100× 8K video wall panels
  - Workstations: 500× with AR/VR capabilities
  - Network: 10 Tbps total capacity
  - Power: 50 MW, 99.9999% availability
  - Security: Tier 4 data center equivalent
  - Cost: $200M per center
  - Timeline: 24 months design and build
  - Operational: Q2 2030
```

4.1.2 10,000-Node Global Network

```
Expansion Strategy:
  - Target: 10,000 nodes globally
  - Distribution: Proportional to energy consumption
  - Density: 1 node per 100 MW of generation/load
  - Manufacturing: 1,000 nodes/month production capacity
  - Deployment: 500 nodes/month installation capacity
  - Cost: $5B total deployment cost

Regional Targets:
  - North America: 3,000 nodes
  - Europe: 2,500 nodes
  - Asia: 3,000 nodes
  - Rest of World: 1,500 nodes

Node Evolution:
  - Quantum: 1024 qubits standard in all major nodes
  - Neuromorphic: 20M neurons standard
  - Communication: 100 Gbps standard, quantum key distribution
  - Power: Self-powered with local renewables + grid
  - Intelligence: Fully autonomous operation with human oversight
```

4.1.3 Global Energy Market Integration

```
Market Platform: Energy Global Exchange (EGE)
  - Participants: 1000+ generators, 100+ grid operators, 10000+ consumers
