  - Features: Demonstration center, customer briefing center
  - Cost: $200M acquisition and build-out
  - Timeline: 2025 acquisition, 2026 operational

Quantum Research Center: Nevada, USA
  - Purpose: Quantum hardware R&D and manufacturing
  - Size: 100,000 sq ft specialized facility
  - Features: Clean rooms, cryogenic facilities, vibration isolation
  - Adjacent: Fusion research facility
  - Cost: $150M construction
  - Timeline: 2025-2026 construction

Neuromorphic Research Center: Austin, Texas
  - Purpose: Neuromorphic hardware R&D and manufacturing
  - Size: 80,000 sq ft specialized facility
  - Features: Chip design labs, testing facilities, fabrication support
  - Adjacent: Major semiconductor fabs
  - Cost: $100M construction
  - Timeline: 2025-2026 construction

European Research Center: Zurich, Switzerland
