10. Deployment & Rollout Strategy

10.1 Deployment Methodology

10.1.1 Phased Rollout Approach

```
Phase A: Alpha Deployment (Internal)
  - Scope: Internal testing by development team
  - Environment: Controlled test environment
  - Duration: 1-2 months per major release
  - Purpose: Find and fix major issues
  - Success Criteria: No critical issues, performance targets met

Phase B: Beta Deployment (Friendly)
  - Scope: Selected friendly customers/partners
  - Environment: Their production environment but limited scope
  - Duration: 1-3 months per major release
  - Purpose: Real-world testing, user feedback
  - Success Criteria: Users successful, no major issues

Phase C: Limited Release (Early Adopters)
  - Scope: Early adopter customers
  - Environment: Full production but limited geography/functionality
  - Duration: 3-6 months per major release
  - Purpose: Scale testing, operational procedures
  - Success Criteria: Reliability targets met, customer satisfaction high

Phase D: General Availability
  - Scope: All customers
  - Environment: Full production, full functionality
  - Duration: Ongoing
  - Purpose: Business as usual
  - Success Criteria: Business metrics met
```

10.1.2 Deployment Techniques

```
Blue-Green Deployment:
  - Approach: Two identical environments, switch traffic between them
  - Benefits: Zero downtime, easy rollback
  - Use: For major software updates
  - Requirements: Double infrastructure during deployment

Canary Deployment:
  - Approach: Deploy to small subset first, gradually expand
  - Benefits: Risk limited to small subset
  - Use: For new features, risky changes
  - Monitoring: Intensive monitoring during canary phase

Feature Flags:
  - Approach: Features hidden behind flags, enabled selectively
  - Benefits: Deploy code without enabling features
  - Use: For gradual feature rollout, A/B testing
  - Management: Centralized feature flag management

Rolling Update:
  - Approach: Update instances one at a time
  - Benefits: No double infrastructure needed
  - Use: For routine updates, non-critical systems
  - Risk: Mixed versions during update
```

10.2 Site Deployment Process

10.2.1 Pre-Deployment Activities

```
Month -3: Site Selection
  - Criteria: Grid connection, renewable resources, security, accessibility
  - Process: Site surveys, feasibility studies, negotiations
  - Deliverable: Site selection report and agreement

Month -2: Design
  - Activities: Detailed site design, engineering drawings
  - Considerations: Power requirements, network connectivity, environmental
  - Deliverable: Complete site design package

Month -1: Preparation
  - Activities: Site preparation, utility connections, permits
  - Resources: Local contractors, equipment delivery
  - Deliverable: Site ready for equipment installation

Week -1: Final Checks
  - Activities: Site inspection, safety checks, final approvals
  - Verification: All requirements met, no showstoppers
  - Deliverable: Site readiness certification
```

10.2.2 Installation Process

```
Day 1: Equipment Delivery and Staging
  - Morning: Equipment delivery and unloading
  - Afternoon: Equipment staging and inspection
  - Evening: Security setup for overnight

Day 2: Physical Installation
  - Morning: Rack installation, power distribution
  - Afternoon: Equipment mounting, cabling
  - Evening: Physical installation verification

Day 3: Power and Network
  - Morning: Power connections, testing
  - Afternoon: Network connections, testing
  - Evening: Basic connectivity established

Day 4: Software Installation
  - Morning: Operating system installation
  - Afternoon: Application software installation
  - Evening: Basic functionality testing

Day 5: Configuration and Integration
  - Morning: System configuration
  - Afternoon: Integration with central systems
  - Evening: End-to-end testing

Day 6: Testing and Optimization
  - All day: Comprehensive testing
  - Evening: Performance optimization

Day 7: Final Verification and Handover
  - Morning: Final testing and verification
  - Afternoon: Documentation, training
  - Evening: Handover to operations team
```

10.2.3 Post-Deployment Activities

```
Week 1: Monitoring and Support
  - Activities: Intensive monitoring, on-site support
  - Focus: Stability, performance, any issues
  - Resources: Deployment team on-site

Week 2-4: Optimization and Fine-Tuning
  - Activities: Performance optimization, fine-tuning
  - Focus: Achieving optimal performance
  - Resources: Remote support with occasional on-site

Month 2-3: Normal Operations
  - Activities: Regular monitoring, routine maintenance
  - Focus: Reliability, meeting service levels
  - Resources: Remote monitoring and support

Ongoing: Continuous Improvement
  - Activities: Software updates, hardware upgrades
  - Focus: Keeping current, improving performance
  - Resources: Regular maintenance visits
```

