12. Security Implementation Plan

12.1 Security Architecture Implementation

12.1.1 Zero Trust Implementation

```
Identity and Access Management:
  - Multi-factor Authentication: Required for all access
  - Certificate-based Authentication: For machine-to-machine
  - Role-Based Access Control: Least privilege principle
  - Continuous Verification: Re-authentication based on risk
  - Implementation: Phase 1 (2025) for internal, Phase 2 (2026) for external

Network Segmentation:
  - Microsegmentation: Each device in its own segment
  - Software-Defined Perimeters: Dynamic network boundaries
  - Quantum Network Isolation: Separate quantum control networks
  - Implementation: Phase 1 (2025) design, Phase 2 (2026) deployment

Device Security:
  - Hardware Root of Trust: In all devices
  - Secure Boot: Verified boot process
  - Remote Attestation: Continuous verification of device integrity
  - Implementation: Phase 1 (2025) design, Phase 2 (2026) in manufacturing
```

12.1.2 Cryptography Implementation

```
Post-Quantum Cryptography Migration:
  - Assessment: Inventory of all cryptographic usage (2025)
  - Planning: Migration roadmap (2025)
  - Implementation: Hybrid classical+PQ (2026-2027)
  - Completion: Full PQ (2028-2029)

Quantum Key Distribution:
  - Backbone: QKD between major facilities (2026-2027)
  - Regional: QKD within regions (2028-2029)
  - Global: Satellite QKD (2030-2031)
  - Integration: With existing encryption (TLS, IPsec)

Key Management:
  - Hardware Security Modules: For key generation and storage
  - Key Lifecycle Management: Automated key rotation
  - Key Distribution: Secure distribution mechanisms
  - Implementation: Phase 1 (2025) design, Phase 2 (2026) deployment
```

12.1.3 Security Monitoring Implementation

```
Security Information and Event Management:
  - Collection: From all systems and devices (2025-2026)
  - Correlation: Real-time correlation of events (2026-2027)
  - Analytics: Machine learning for anomaly detection (2027-2028)
  - Response: Automated response playbooks (2028-2029)

Threat Intelligence:
  - Collection: From multiple sources (2025-2026)
  - Integration: With monitoring systems (2026-2027)
  - Automation: Automated IOC matching and blocking (2027-2028)
  - Sharing: With partners and ISACs (2028-2029)

Vulnerability Management:
  - Scanning: Continuous vulnerability scanning (2025-2026)
  - Prioritization: Risk-based prioritization (2026-2027)
  - Remediation: Automated patching where possible (2027-2028)
  - Validation: Verification of remediation (2028-2029)
```

12.2 Physical Security Implementation

12.2.1 Facility Security

```
Quantum Facilities:
  - Perimeter: 3-meter fence with intrusion detection
  - Access: Mantrap with biometric + card + PIN
  - Surveillance: 100% coverage with AI analytics
  - Materials: TEMPEST-rated construction
  - Implementation: Phase 1 (2025-2026) for first facilities

Data Centers:
  - Access: Multi-factor with security escort for visitors
  - Monitoring: 24/7 security personnel
  - Environmental: Fire suppression, flood detection
  - Redundancy: Multiple geographically separated sites
  - Implementation: Phase 1 (2025-2026) for first data centers

Edge Locations:
  - Enclosures: Tamper-resistant, environmentally sealed
  - Sensors: Tamper detection, environmental monitoring
  - Communication: Encrypted, with intrusion detection
  - Remote Disable: Ability to disable if compromised
  - Implementation: Phase 2 (2026-2027) for edge deployment
```

12.2.2 Supply Chain Security

```
Component Verification:
  - Source Verification: Trusted suppliers only
  - Component Testing: Testing for backdoors/tampering
  - Chain of Custody: Tracked from manufacture to deployment
  - Implementation: Phase 1 (2025) for critical components

Manufacturing Security:
  - Secure Facilities: Manufacturing in secure facilities
  - Personnel Screening: Background checks for all personnel
  - Process Controls: Strict controls on manufacturing processes
  - Implementation: Phase 2 (2026-2027) for volume manufacturing

Deployment Security:
  - Secure Transport: Tamper-evident packaging, tracked transport
  - Installation Verification: Verification after installation
  - Ongoing Verification: Continuous verification of integrity
  - Implementation: Phase 2 (2026-2027) for volume deployment
```

12.3 Compliance Implementation

12.3.1 Grid Security Compliance

```
NERC CIP (North America):
  - CIP-002: Critical Cyber Asset Identification (2025)
  - CIP-003: Security Management Controls (2025)
  - CIP-004: Personnel & Training (2025)
  - CIP-005: Electronic Security Perimeter (2026)
  - CIP-006: Physical Security (2026)
  - CIP-007: System Security Management (2026)
  - CIP-008: Incident Reporting (2026)
  - CIP-009: Recovery Plans (2026)
  - CIP-010: Configuration Change Management (2027)
  - CIP-011: Information Protection (2027)
  - CIP-014: Physical Security (2027)

IEC 62443 (International):
  - Part 2-1: Security program requirements (2025)
  - Part 2-4: Security program requirements for IACS service providers (2025)
  - Part 3-3: System security requirements (2026)
  - Part 4-1: Secure product development lifecycle (2026)
  - Part 4-2: Technical security requirements (2027)
  - Certification: SL 3 for critical components (2028)
```

12.3.2 Data Protection Compliance

```
GDPR (Europe):
  - Data Mapping: Understanding all personal data (2025)
  - Legal Basis: Establishing legal basis for processing (2025)
  - Individual Rights: Procedures for individual rights (2026)
  - Data Protection by Design: Built into systems (2026-2027)
  - Documentation: Maintaining required documentation (ongoing)

CCPA/CPRA (California):
  - Consumer Rights: Procedures for consumer rights (2025)
  - Data Inventory: Inventory of personal information (2025)
  - Opt-Out: Mechanism for opt-out of sale (2026)
  - Service Provider Agreements: With all service providers (2026)

Other Regions:
  - China: Cybersecurity Law, Personal Information Protection Law
  - Brazil: LGPD
  - India: Personal Data Protection Bill
  - Implementation: As we expand to each region
```

